  "response": "To solve the mathematical expression \\(7 + \\frac{7}{7} + 7 \\times 7 - 7\\), we need to follow the order of operations, commonly known by the acronym PEMDAS (Parentheses, Exponents, Multiplication and Division (from left to right), Addition and Subtraction (from left to right)).\n\n1. Multiplication and Division (from left to right):\n   \\[\n   7 + \\frac{7}{7} + 7 \\times 7 - 7\n   \\]\n   \\[\n   7 + 1 + 49 - 7\n   \\]\n\n2. Addition and Subtraction (from left to right):\n   \\[\n   7 + 1 = 8\n   \\]\n   \\[\n   8 + 49 = 57\n   \\]\n   \\[\n   57 - 7 = 50\n   \\]\n\nTherefore, the answer is \\(\\boxed{50}\\).",
